HEADWORD: Photoxylography
<hw>Pho`to*xy*log"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + <ets>xylography</ets>.]</ety> <def>The process
of producing a representation of an object on wood, by photography, for
the use of the wood engraver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

